
Pinto beans


### Chris

* 1 lb pinto beans
* 1 onion, roughly chopped
* 4 cloves garlic
* 2 jalapenos, seeded, sliced
* jalapeno pickle juice (or vinegar)
* meat broth or water

* salt to taste

* salt pork (or bacon, diced)

* cilantro?
* cumin / chile powder / ancho?


### Range Beans
### Perini p. 155

* 1 lb pinto beans
* 1/4 lb salt pork
* 3-4 cloves garlic
* 1 T chile powder

* Cut pork into thin strips and rinse
* cover beans with water, add pork and garlic
* when beans are tender, season with salt and chile powder



### Homesick Texan
### Jalapeno Pinto Beans p. 122

* 1 lb pinto beans
* 1 medium yellow onion, cut in half
* 4 cloves garlic
* 1 jalapeno, seeded / stemmed, cut in half lengthwise
* 1/4 cup white vinegar / jalapeno pickle juice
* salt


### Ranch-style beans
### Fearing p.265?

* 3 cups pinto beans (soaked overnight)
* 2 quarts ham hock broth (or water)
* 1 onion, diced
* 2 cloves garlic, minced
* 2 medium tomatoes, blanched, peeled, seeded, diced
* 3 ounces bacon, diced
* 2 Tbsp chile powder
* 1 tsp ground cumin
* 1 tbsp ancho chile puree
* 1/4 cup ketchup




### NYTimes
### Drunken beans, p. 287

* 2 slices bacon
* 1 onion, diced
* 2 cloves garlic, minced
* 2 cups dried pinto beans
* 4 cups chicken broth
* 2 cups beer
* 2-4 jalapenos, thinly sliced
* 2 Tbsp chopped cilantro
